    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but there isn't anyone left to care, that's the thing. i'm just waiting for a phone call that's never coming. and it doesn't feel \"senseless\" to me, it feels like the only thing i have any say in anymore. i've lost my health, my friends, my independence... at least if i chose it, it would be my own choice. doesn't everyone deserve some kind of dignity in the end? even if that means choosing when to let go?",
